{"heading":"Wars are born of lusts—The friends of the world are the enemies of God—Sin is failure to walk in the light we have received.","number":4,"verseCount":17,"verses":[[1,["From whence ",["come",["clarity-word"]]," ",["wars",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG War","tg/war"],"."]]]," and ",["fightings",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Apostasy of the Early Christian Church","tg/apostasy-of-the-early-christian-church"],"."]]]," among you? ",["come they",["clarity-word"]]," not hence, ",["even",["clarity-word"]]," of your ",["lusts",["study-note-ref","c",["GR pleasures, gratifications, passions."]]]," that war in your members?"]],[2,["Ye lust, and have not: ye kill, and desire to have, and cannot obtain: ye fight and war, yet ye have not, because ye ask not."]],[3,["Ye ",["ask",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Prayer","tg/prayer"],"."]]],", and receive not, because ye ",["ask",["study-note-ref","b",[["Hel. 10:5 (4–6)","bofm/hel/10.5"],"."]]]," ",["amiss",["study-note-ref","c",["GR wickedly, wrongly. ",["Rom. 8:26 (26–27)","nt/rom/8.26"],"; ",["D&C 46:30 (28–30)","dc-testament/dc/46.30"],"; ",["88:65 (64–65)","dc-testament/dc/88.65"],"."]]],", that ye may ",["consume",["study-note-ref","d",["GR waste, expend. ",["D&C 46:9","dc-testament/dc/46.9"],"."]]]," ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," upon your ",["lusts",["study-note-ref","e",[["TG Lust","tg/lust"],"."]]],"."]],[4,["Ye ",["adulterers",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Whore","tg/whore"],"."]]]," and adulteresses, ",["",1542],"know ye not that the friendship of the ",["world",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG World","tg/world"],"; ",["Worldliness","tg/worldliness"],"."]]]," is ",["enmity",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Opposition","tg/opposition"],"."]]]," with God? whosoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the ",["enemy",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Enemies","tg/enemies"],"."]]]," of God."]],[5,["Do ye think that the scripture saith in vain, The spirit that dwelleth in us lusteth to ",["envy",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Envy","tg/envy"],"."]]],"?"]],[6,["But he giveth more ",["grace",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Grace","tg/grace"],"."]]],". Wherefore he saith, God resisteth the ",["proud",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Pride","tg/pride"],"."]]],", but giveth grace unto the ",["humble",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Poor in Spirit","tg/poor-in-spirit"],"."]]],"."]],[7,[["Submit",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Reconciliation","tg/reconciliation"],"; ",["Submissiveness","tg/submissiveness"],"."]]]," yourselves therefore to God. ",["Resist",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Abstain","tg/abstain"],"; ",["Self-Mastery","tg/self-mastery"],"."]]]," the ",["devil",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Devil","tg/devil"],"."]]],", and he will flee from you."]],[8,[["Draw",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG God, Presence of","tg/god-presence-of"],"."]]]," ",["nigh",["study-note-ref","b",[["Ps. 69:18","ot/ps/69.18"],"; ",["D&C 88:63","dc-testament/dc/88.63"],"."]]]," to God, and he will draw nigh to you. ",["Cleanse",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Repent","tg/repent"],"."]]]," ",["your",["clarity-word"]]," hands, ",["ye",["clarity-word"]]," sinners; and ",["purify",["study-note-ref","d",[["TG Purification","tg/purification"],"; ",["Purity","tg/purity"],"."]]]," ",["your",["clarity-word"]]," hearts, ",["ye",["clarity-word"]]," double minded."]],[9,[["Be afflicted",["study-note-ref","a",["GR Endure hardship, Suffer harassment."]]],", and mourn, and ",["weep",["study-note-ref","b",[["Isa. 22:12","ot/isa/22.12"],"; ",["Joel 2:17","ot/joel/2.17"],"; ",["2 Cor. 7:10","nt/2-cor/7.10"],"."]]],": let your laughter be turned to ",["mourning",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Mourning","tg/mourning"],"."]]],", and ",["your",["clarity-word"]]," joy to heaviness."]],[10,[["Humble",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Contrite Heart","tg/contrite-heart"],"; ",["Humility","tg/humility"],"."]]]," yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he shall lift you up."]],[11,[["Speak",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Gossip","tg/gossip"],"."]]]," not evil one of another, brethren. He that speaketh evil of ",["his",["clarity-word"]]," brother, and judgeth his brother, speaketh evil of the ",["law",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Citizenship","tg/citizenship"],"."]]],", and judgeth the law: but if thou judge the law, thou art not a doer of the law, but a judge."]],[12,["There is one lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy: who art thou that ",["judgest",["study-note-ref","a",[["Morm. 8:20 (19–20)","bofm/morm/8.20"],"."]]]," another?"]],[13,["Go to now, ye that say, To day or to ",["morrow",["study-note-ref","a",[["Prov. 27:1","ot/prov/27.1"],"."]]]," we will go into such a city, and continue there a year, and buy and sell, and get gain:"]],[14,["Whereas ye know not what ",["shall be",["clarity-word"]]," on the morrow. For what ",["is",["clarity-word"]]," your life? It is even a ",["vapour",["study-note-ref","a",[["1 Cor. 7:31 (29–31)","nt/1-cor/7.31"],"; ",["Jacob 7:26","bofm/jacob/7.26"],"."]]],", that appeareth for a little time, and then vanisheth away."]],[15,["For that ye ",["ought",["clarity-word"]]," to say, If the Lord will, we shall live, and do this, or that."]],[16,["But now ye rejoice in your ",["boastings",["study-note-ref","a",[["TG Boast","tg/boast"],"."]]],": all such rejoicing is evil."]],[17,["Therefore to him that ",["knoweth",["study-note-ref","a",[["Luke 12:47","nt/luke/12.47"],"; ",["2 Ne. 9:25 (25–27)","bofm/2-ne/9.25"],"."]]]," to do good, and ",["doeth",["study-note-ref","b",[["TG Disobedience","tg/disobedience"],"; ",["Good Works","tg/good-works"],"; ",["Obedience","tg/obedience"],"."]]]," ",["it",["clarity-word"]]," not, to him it is ",["sin",["study-note-ref","c",[["TG Sin","tg/sin"],"."]]],"."]]],"volume":"nt"}